explanation: This solution uses two pointers, i and j, to traverse the strings s and t respectively. It checks if the current character in s matches the current character in t, and if it does, it moves the pointer in s forward. If the current character in s does not match the current character in t, it simply moves the pointer in t forward. The function returns true if all characters in s are found in t in the same order, and false otherwise.

